com.github.fedorov_s_n.graphs

Class Graph<V,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.fedorov_s_n.graphs.Graph<V,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - type of vertices parameters
    E - type of edges parameters
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public final class Graph<V,E>
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    Directed graph with parametrized vertices and edges. Graph is supposed to be effectively immutable though it's possible to mutate vertices and edges lists.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Graph

        public Graph(List<Vertex<V,E>> vertices,
             List<Edge<V,E>> edges)
        Create graph from given vertex and edge lists. Input collections are neither checked nor copied. User is supposed to care about ummutability himself.

        Performs indexing on vertices so creating is not a functional call.

        Parameters:
        vertices - list of vertices
        edges - list of edges

    • Method Detail

      • fromEdges

        public static <V,E> Graph<V,E> fromEdges(List<Edge<V,E>> edges)
        Create graph from given edge list. Vertex list is calculated as all edges' parents and children. Input list are neither checked nor copied. User is supposed to care about ummutability himself.

        Performs indexing on vertices so creating is not a functional call.

        Parameters:
        edges - list of edges

      • filter

        public <T> Graph<T,E> filter(Class<T> bound,
                             Predicate<T> test)
        Creates new graph that has vertices of this graph if parameter is instance of specified class or null. Edges are changed accordingly, ruled by onRemove function. All vertices and edges are actually new objects, not shared with this graph.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of bound
        Parameters:
        bound - class that should be ancestor of all vertices parameters
        test - predicate over T
        Returns:
        new graph

      • propagate

        public Graph<V,E> propagate(Predicate<Vertex<V,E>> vertexPredicate,
                            Predicate<Edge<V,E>> edgePredicate,
                            BiFunction<E,E,E> merger)
        Creates new graph that has vertices of this graph that passes through collection filter. Removes all child and parent edges of removed vertex and creates new edges from every parent to every child. Edge parameter is calculated as function of parent and child edge parameters. All vertices and edges in new graph are new objects, not shared with this graph.
        Parameters:
        vertexPredicate - function that determines if vertex should persist in new graph
        edgePredicate - function that determines if edge should persist or be generated in new graph
        merger - function to calculate created edge parameter
        Returns:
        new graph

      • dfs

        public Vertex<V,E> dfs(Collection<Vertex<V,E>> startNodes,
                       Function<Vertex<V,E>,Stream<Vertex<V,E>>> upd,
                       Consumer<Vertex<V,E>> onEnter,
                       Predicate<Vertex<V,E>> onStart,
                       Predicate<Vertex<V,E>> onFinish,
                       Consumer<Vertex<V,E>> onExit)
        Traverse graph with depth-first search until the requested vertex is found or there are no nodes to continue scanning.
        Parameters:
        startNodes - collection of nodes to start traverse
        upd - function to return stream of vertices to go
        onEnter - function that is executed when another vertex is polled from start collection
        onStart - function that is executed on enter to vertex, should return true if vertex fits under criteria and should be returned by the method; false otherwise
        onFinish - function that is executed on exit from vertex, should return true if vertex fits under criteria and should be returned by the method; false otherwise
        onExit - function that is executed when there are no more vertices in current sub-traverse
        Returns:
        the first vertex fitting under onStart or onFinish criteria or null if there are no such vertex
